The paper deals with face detection, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). It specifically focuses on surveillance images, which falls under the category of computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also mentions the use of benchmarking platforms and comparative performance analysis, which suggests a machine learning (cs.MM) and statistical learning (cs.LG) approach. Finally, the paper proposes a new method for face detection, which involves leveraging body information, indicating an artificial intelligence (cs.AI) subcategory.
